  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Castor is a fantastic family-run hotel - perfect for a cosy mountain getaway. Its great atmosphere, impromptu music nights in the lounge and professional wine tastings, make this one of the liveliest hotels in Champoluc.</p>
<h2>Service that goes above and beyond </h2>
<p>You'll be treated like an old friend when you stay at Hotel Castor. Whether you're tucking into a filling breakfast or chilling out in the cosy bar at the end of the day, you'll find a friendly face and some great local knowledge. The hotel's owner, Herman, loves music and occasionally hosts an off the cuff live music night in the bar. All the locals pack in and the atmosphere is electric! Most weekends there's a lunchtime barbeque where you can relax in the sun with some local food (payable locally) and during the first week of August, you'll find live jazz in the garden every evening.</p>
<h2>Perfect for exploring Champoluc </h2>
<p>This hotel couldn't be more perfectly located. It's right in the centre of Champoluc and a short walk from the village's bars, restaurants and chairlift. Take a ride to the top for a day of exploring the walking trails and taking in the stunning scenery. Especially the magnificent views of the Monte Rosa mountains and glacier. Looking to explore further? The bus stop's just 50 metres from the hotel so it's just as easy to get around the local area.</p>
<p><strong>Transfer time:</strong> approx. 2 hours by coach from Milan airport. </p>]]></description>
